 Kley argues that Reform Catholicism, not a secular Enlightenment, provided the justification for Catholic kings to suppress a society instituted by the papacy. Spanning the years from the mid†‘sixteenth century to the onset of the French Revolution, and the Jesuit presence from China to Brazil, this is the only single volume in English to make coherent sense of the series of expulsions that add up to what was arguably the most important religious event in Europe of the time, resulting in the secularization of tens of thousands of Jesuits.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 0aEnlightenmentzEurope. 7aRELIGION / Christian Church / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311063899840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300235616423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300235616/original  a978-3-11-063899-8  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles